  "body": "In https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/37680, @phillip-kruger introduced a dependency to `quarkus-rest-server-spi-deployment` in `quarkus-vertx-http-deployment`.\r\n\r\nProblem is  `quarkus-rest-server-spi-deployment` depends on `io.quarkus.resteasy.reactive:resteasy-reactive-processor` which depends on `io.quarkus.resteasy.reactive:resteasy-reactive`.\r\n\r\nSo by doing that, we added RESTEasy Reactive to the deployment classpath of nearly every Quarkus app.\r\n\r\nI don't think we want to do that.\r\n\r\nI don't know exactly why   `quarkus-rest-server-spi-deployment` depends on `io.quarkus.resteasy.reactive:resteasy-reactive-processor` but that's probably something that we need to fix.\r\n\r\nAnd I think we need to fix it before I build the 3.9 core artifacts.\r\n\r\n(And yes I stumbled upon that testing something completely different, that's what we call luck)\r\n\r\n/cc @geoand @cescoffier @phillip-kruger @maxandersen ",
